<title>NetBSD/i386 on ASUS EeePC</title>
</head>

<sect1 id="eee-supported">
  <title>Supported Hardware</title>
  
  <para>
    The following hardware components can be found inside the
    EeePC 701 and 900. Information here includes what drivers
    support the hardware component, if any is present in NetBSD.
  </para>

  <informaltable id="eee-supported-tab">
    <tgroup cols="4">
      <thead>
	<row>
	  <entry>Device</entry>
	  <entry>Driver</entry>
	  <entry>Available in </entry>
	  <entry>Comment </entry>
	</row>
      </thead>

      <tbody>
	<row>
	  <entry> Ethernet:</entry>
	  <entry> lii(4) </entry>
	  <entry> 4.1 </entry>
	  <entry> - </entry>
	</row>

	<row>
	  <entry> WiFi: </entry>
	  <entry> ath(4) </entry>
	  <entry> - </entry>
	  <entry> Works with the following <ulink url="http://ftp.NetBSD.org/pub/NetBSD/misc/jmcneill/atheee.patch">patch</ulink> </entry>
	</row>

	<row>
	  <entry> Webcam: </entry>
	  <entry> uvideo(4) </entry>
	  <entry> 5.0 </entry>
	  <entry> USB Video Class </entry>
	</row>

	<row>
	  <entry> Suspend to RAM:</entry>
	  <entry> acpi(4) </entry>
	  <entry> 5.0 </entry>
	  <entry> - </entry>
	</row>

	<row>
	  <entry> Display: </entry>
	  <entry> X.org and XFree86, both i810 and Intel drivers</entry>
	  <entry> 4.0 </entry>
	  <entry> <filename role="pkg">x11/xf86-video-i810</filename>, <filename role="pkg">x11/xf86-video-intel</filename>  </entry>
	</row>

	<row>
	  <entry> Hardware-3D: </entry>
	  <entry> i915drm</entry>
	  <entry> 4.0</entry>
	  <entry> - </entry>
	</row>

	<row>
	  <entry> Audio:</entry>
	  <entry> azalia(4) </entry>
	  <entry> 5.0 </entry>
	  <entry> - </entry>
	</row>

	<row>
	  <entry> USB:</entry>
	  <entry> umass(4) etc.</entry>
	  <entry> 4.0 </entry>
	  <entry> - </entry>
	</row>

	<row>
	  <entry> SD Slot:</entry>
	  <entry> umass(4)</entry>
	  <entry> 4.0 </entry>
	  <entry> - </entry>
	</row>

	<row>
	  <entry> Fn keys:</entry>
	  <entry> asus(4)</entry>
	  <entry> 5.0 </entry>
	  <entry> Volume, brightness control </entry>
	</row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>
</sect1>

<sect1 id="eeepc_installing_i386">
  <title>Installing NetBSD on a EeePC</title>

  <para>
    You can boot your EeePC from the network as described in our
    <ulink url="../../docs/network/netboot/">Netboot HowTo</ulink>. After that, you can do a
    normal network install. 
  </para>

  <para>
    The usual steps to reduce power consumption as outlined in our 
    <ulink url="../../docs/power-mgmt/">Power Management
    documentation</ulink> apply. 
  </para>
</sect1>

